    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-03-21T04:10:19+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-21T04:10:19+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-20T17:40:19Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-20T17:40:19Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure will persist across the state. The high pressure centre associated with the ridge will become established in the Tasman Sea over the weekend. A trough moves over the south early next week with a cold front clipping the southeast mid week. A new ridge develops south of the Bight early to mid next week.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW005" description="Lower South East" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-03-21T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-22T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-20T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-21T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog. Sunny afternoon. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the middle of the day then tending southeast to southwesterly in the late afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures in the mid to high 20s.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:00am to 4:20pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-03-22T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-23T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-21T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-22T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog. Mostly sunny afternoon. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h in the middle of the day then tending southeast to southwesterly in the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 10 with daytime temperatures reaching 24 to 29.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-03-23T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-24T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-22T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-23T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of morning fog near the coast. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending southeast to southwesterly during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 12 with daytime temperatures reaching 26 to 31.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-03-24T00:00:00+10:30" end-time-local="2026-03-25T00:00:00+10:30" start-time-utc="2026-03-23T13:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-03-24T13:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. The chance of a thunderstorm near the eastern border in the afternoon. Light winds becoming west to southwesterly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to around 14 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
